1. Download, parse and validate config from JSON file: https://api.example.com/config.json
2. Connect to the cloud with GET request using the key and URL provided in response of 1.
3. Try connecting to one of IoT devices (http://192.168.x.x), if successful then connect to it otherwise connect to the next available device. Also print out the response for each connection.
4. Store all requests made by your Flutter app in one collection, and use that collection to fetch response (GET request) using https://api.example.com/request/\<id\>/\<key\>
5. On every 20 minutes, update request collection in https://api.example.com/request/\<id\>/\<key\> with a PUT request. The new collection should replace the previous one in the response.